Parse Pmetrics output

Source: R/PM_parse.R
PM_parse.Rd

A flexible parser for Pmetrics output

Usage

PM_parse(path = ".", fit = "fit.rds", write = TRUE)

Arguments

fit

The relative path to a "fit.rds" file.

write

A logical value indicating if the results should be returned (FALSE, default) or written to disk (TRUE)

wd

The directory containing the output from the Rust-implementation of NPAG

Value

The output of PM_parse is a list containing the following elements

  • op Written to the standard of PM_op()

  • pop Written to the standard of PM_pop()

  • post Written to the standard of PM_post()

  • cycles Written to the standard of PM_cycle()

  • final Written to the standard of PM_final()

  • cov Written to the standard of PM_cov()

Details

Currently written for the Rust implementation of NPAG

Author

Michael Neely and Markus Hovd
